cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.CY, cs.DB. 

The paper uses social network analysis to study the structure and resilience of Mafia syndicates, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.DB (Databases). However, given the focus on network analysis and the use of digital trails and judicial documents, cs.SI and cs.CR are the most likely categories.
